<div class="quotetitle">Jedi QuestMaster wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />If four power pads would work I take it 4 zappers would work?<br /></div><br /><br />The zapper light/trigger detect is directly connected, but with the controllers and power pad it is a stream of serial bits.  Different enough to require a select switch on the Satellite.<br /><br />Well, I looked up the manual:<br />"* The NES Four Score cannot be used with the NES Zapper (R) or NES Power Pad (R)."<br /><a href="http://www.nesworld.com/manuals/fourscor.txt" class="postlink">http://www.nesworld.com/manuals/fourscor.txt</a><br /><br />Damn, there goes the idea for the "COPS" game where you use a powerpad, zapper, and powerglove all at once.<br /><br />With 4 powerpads, you could make a small power-padded room where you could jump Mario-style and hit the ceiling.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=10">Memblers</a> — Tue Sep 14, 2010 6:29 pm</p><hr />
